The paper discusses a question-answering task in clinical medicine using NLP techniques, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed solution, SeaReader, is an end-to-end reading comprehension model based on LSTM networks and attention architecture, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). The model also integrates information across multiple documents, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
